A nationwide study of the blood of more than 28,000 people found that, as of July, approximately 9.3% in the US had antibodies to the novel coronavirus.

The numbers ranged from an average of 3.5% in the West to an average of 27% in the Northeast. https://t.co/2BTCAaiqBg
